      "id": "RQ-0008",
      "status": "done",
      "title": "Fix machine run loop idle and blocked summaries",
      "description": "Repair the machine contract for `ralph machine run loop` so idle, no-candidate, blocked, stalled, stopped, failed, and completed states remain distinct all the way to terminal machine summaries and RalphMac Run Control. Today several non-success operator states return `Ok(())` from the shared loop implementation and the machine command emits `outcome: \"completed\"` with no `blocking`, which lets the Swift app clear or hide useful operator state. The desired outcome is a loop-level outcome model with blocking-aware summaries that match the semantics already expected from `machine run one`.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "machine-api",
        "run-loop",
        "ralphmac",
        "blocking",
        "ux"
      ],
